Hello,

I put an alpha-test version of Objective Caml for MacOS in
<ftp://ftp.inria.fr/lang/caml-light/ocaml-2.00-mac-1.0a1.sea.bin>.

This is the O'Caml toplevel running in a window, integrated with a
small text editor for your source files.

A lot of features are missing, but it is pretty usable already (the
graphics library is fully implemented).

It presently runs only on PowerPC machines.


